There are very few story lines that are so worth watching and sharing.

reviewText: Thank god that at last it looks as though our dreams have come true with whoever it is bringing out the remaining seasons of TBAA.Maybe God wrote the powers that be a letter!!!.When I watch them I will think of the beautiful John Dye who sadly passed away last year.I adored him in his role of Andrew the Angel of Death, I am so very very sorry he is no longer with us. He is with the real angels now.God Bless You John....You will be in my heart forever.

reviewText: I started with the first season and am working my way through all of them.  I watch one episode every night at bedtime to impress my subconscious.  The episodes are well written and each one has a lesson.  I can hardly wait until bedtime when I get to view another episode.  You've got to fall in love with the angels.

reviewText: So happy another season was released!  We enjoy watching an episode when there isn't anything decent on tv, which is often these days!  It is a timeless message that most of us never get tired of hearing!  So sad there isn't more quality programs on tv like this one.  So many channels, so little to watch!  Even the news gets boring after awhile!  Thanks so much for this release.  I do think it is a bit pricey but we will watch it many times over!
